{
  "text": "The photosynthetic apparatus in MIT9313 is organized in two supercomplexes in complete media: a naked PSI-trimer and a PSII-dimer surrounded by 8 lightharvesting subunits (PcbB). The peripheral antennae in the photosynthetic membranes are two types: associated with the photosystems (fixed antenna) forming supercomplexes or as mobile antenna subjected to light regulation. Under iron depletion, the photosynthetic membranes of MIT9313 have PSI trimers that are surrounded by 18 light-harvesting proteins of PcbA [CITATION_1] . PSII is a supercomplex formed by a dimeric PSII with up to 8 light-harvesting proteins (PcbB) in both media [CITATION_2] . We used CN-PAGE to detect and to estimate the quantity of the supercomplexes of the photosynthetic apparatus. The supercomplexes can be extracted and isolated from the photosynthetic membrane and dissociate during the solubilization with detergent and during the centrifugation that precedes the electrophoresis.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "4335506",
    "[CITATION_2]": "4335506"
